# [PROJECT_NAME] — Git Workflow Standards

> Category: Standards · Complexity: Simple · Prerequisite: basic git knowledge

Source-control conventions for this repo. Downstream automation parses this file, so keep
headings and the machine-readable formats below intact.

## Working loop

Four steps per change:

1. Branch off an up-to-date main.
   ```bash
   git switch main && git pull
   git switch -c feature/[name]
   ```
2. Commit incrementally as work lands: `git add [files]` then `git commit -m "[message]"`.
3. Push the branch: `git push -u origin [branch]`.
4. Open a PR (host UI or CLI — see `.ai-run/guides/project.md`).

## Branch naming

| Type    | Pattern           | Role                     |
| ------- | ----------------- | ------------------------ |
| Main    | `main`            | production               |
| Feature | `feature/[name]`  | new work                 |
| Bugfix  | `bugfix/[name]`   | defect fixes             |
| Hotfix  | `hotfix/[name]`   | urgent production fixes  |

